Q1. Sales % by Region
Show each salesperson's sale amount and what percentage of their region's total sales they contributed. Round the percentage to 2 decimal places.
SELECT
  region,
  salesperson,
  amount,
  ROUND(amount * 100.0 / SUM(amount) OVER (PARTITION BY region), 2) AS pct_of_region
FROM sales
ORDER BY region, amount DESC;






Q2. Salary Ratio to Dept Avg
For each employee, show their salary and their ratio to the department average. A ratio of 1.2 means 20% above the department average. Round to 2 decimals.

SELECT
  dept,
  name,
  salary,
  ROUND(salary * 1.0 / AVG(salary) OVER (PARTITION BY dept), 2) AS ratio_to_dept_avg
FROM employees
ORDER BY dept, salary DESC;
